								<div class="elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix">
				<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Lucidia Metaverse is one of the top candidates for the best crypto of 2023. Its platform puts a lot of focus on security and managing digital identities. By using a Self-Sovereign Data Store (SSDS) SDK, Lucidia makes sure that its users&#8217; credentials can be stored and accessed safely.</span></p><p> </p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Some of the most important parts of Lucidia Metaverse&#8217;s security system are:</span></p><p> </p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Account Creation and Encrypting Data: The SSDS SDK is in charge of creating accounts, encrypting data, and managing Vault access. Key Stretching algorithms like Scrypt or PBKDF2 are used to encrypt the username and password that users use to get into the Vault.</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Key Rotation: The SDK makes it easy to change keys to keep security going.</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Decentralized OAuth 2.0 Single Sign-On (SSO): The CentraPass decentralized OAuth 2.0 SSO flow is managed by the SDK, giving users a smooth and safe experience.</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Verifiable Credentials: Verifiable credentials are stored in the SSDS and signed by trusted parties. Issuers can make them and give them to users to own or store.</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Lucidia DID SDK: This SDK gives you a strong and safe way to manage digital identities and assets in the metaverse. It has tools for making, changing, and resolving DIDs (unique, persistent, and verifiable digital identities).</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Globally Distributed Key-Value Database: The DID SDK comes with a globally distributed key-value database that stores important information about identities and assets in the metaverse. It acts as a verifiable data registry.</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Schema for Digital Identities and Assets: The schema is made to hold important information for digital content applications like the Unreal Engine or Unity engine. It also has service links for resolving digital assets.</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">By putting in place a complete system for managing digital identities and assets, Lucidia Metaverse ensures that its users&#8217; security is unique, interoperable, persistent, and can&#8217;t be changed.</span></p>					</div>
